					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1621343&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227296" alt="SunnyClockwork" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1621343)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;" >SunnyClockwork</a></span> <span class="odate time_1429073293 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">15 Apr 2015 04:48</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2270833">
									

<p>Thanks! Mistake corrected.</p>
<p>And about the plot&#8230;</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Spoilers(?)</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Not&nbsp;really...</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The Flow is actually a metaphor of the creative process, rather than the actual content of Martha's writing. The idea me and Perelka_L came up with is that maybe artistic creations are all influenced more of less by the Flow as they sometimes get insprations. But AWCY members see, feel or carry out the Flow differently than other people, or manipulate it in certain ways, and that's how they come to create anomalous things (as opposed to using magic or high tech).</p>
<p>What Martha trying to do here is to convey the idea of the Flow to her reader. The changes she made are the process of her creation. And yet, she does not control the Flow, so there's the part of wondering where it comes from.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>I hope the explanation is clear here.</p>

							</div>

								
					
